name: Quick Pot Sticker Soup
author: SLOcook
summary: This quick and delicious soup whips up really quick. I add some egg rolls to round out the meal.
ingredients: 1 (15 ounce) package frozen pot stickers (any filling)
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon of sesame oil in a large pot over medium heat
Stir in the chopped onion and garlic; cook and stir until the onion has softened and turned translucent, about 5 minutes
Pour in the chicken broth, green onions, and remaining sesame oil
Bring to a boil over high heat, and season to taste with salt and pepper
Reduce the heat to medium, and add the frozen pot stickers and stir-fry vegetables
Cook until the pot stickers float, about 8 minutes
